# Prerequisites

Before you begin, ensure you have the following tools and accounts set up.

## Required Software

### Node.js
- **Version**: 18.x or higher (20.x recommended)
- **Download**: https://nodejs.org/
- **Verify installation**:
  ```bash
  node --version  # Should show v18.x.x or higher
  ```

### Package Manager
This project uses **{{packageManager}}** for dependency management.

{{#if (eq packageManager "npm")}}
- **npm** comes bundled with Node.js
- **Verify installation**:
  ```bash
  npm --version  # Should show 9.x.x or higher
  ```
{{else if (eq packageManager "yarn")}}
- **Installation**:
  ```bash
  npm install -g yarn
  ```
- **Verify installation**:
  ```bash
  yarn --version  # Should show 1.22.x or higher
  ```
{{else if (eq packageManager "pnpm")}}
- **Installation**:
  ```bash
  npm install -g pnpm
  ```
- **Verify installation**:
  ```bash
  pnpm --version  # Should show 8.x.x or higher
  ```
{{else if (eq packageManager "bun")}}
- **Installation**: https://bun.sh/docs/installation
- **Verify installation**:
  ```bash
  bun --version  # Should show 1.x.x or higher
  ```
{{/if}}

### Git
- **Version**: 2.x or higher
- **Download**: https://git-scm.com/downloads
- **Verify installation**:
  ```bash
  git --version  # Should show git version 2.x.x
  ```

### Code Editor
We recommend **Visual Studio Code** with the following extensions:
- ESLint
{{#if typescript}}- TypeScript and JavaScript Language Features
{{/if}}{{#if formatting}}- Prettier
{{/if}}{{#if (eq styling "tailwind")}}- Tailwind CSS IntelliSense
{{/if}}{{#if (eq backend "firebase")}}- Firebase
{{/if}}
**Alternative editors**: WebStorm, Sublime Text, or any editor with TypeScript support

## Required Accounts

