## Troubleshooting

### Node.js Version Issues
If you have an older version of Node.js:
- Use [nvm (Node Version Manager)](https://github.com/nvm-sh/nvm) to manage multiple versions
- Install Node.js 20 LTS: `nvm install 20 && nvm use 20`

### Permission Errors
If you encounter permission errors when installing global packages:
- **macOS/Linux**: Use `sudo` carefully or configure npm to use a different directory
- **Windows**: Run terminal as Administrator

{{#if (eq packageManager "pnpm")}}
### pnpm Store Issues
If pnpm store is corrupted:
```bash
pnpm store prune
```
{{/if}}

